net.usikkert.kouinject
Class DefaultInjector

java.lang.Object
  net.usikkert.kouinject.DefaultInjector
All Implemented Interfaces:
Injector
public class DefaultInjector
extends Object
implements Injector

An Injector using classpath scanning to detect beans, and annotations for setup of beans and the dependency injections.

This is the preferred way to use KouInject.

Author:
Christian Ihle

getBean

public <T> T getBean(Class<T> beanClass,
                     String qualifier)
Gets a bean that matches the given class and qualifier.

A bean is considered a match if it's assignable from the bean class, and has the exact same qualifier. If the qualifier is null, then only beans with no qualifier will match. If the qualifier is any then the qualifier match is ignored.

Specified by:
getBean in interface Injector
Type Parameters:
T - The bean will be cast to the type specified.
Parameters:
beanClass - The class to get a bean for.
qualifier - The qualifier for the bean to get. Can be null.
Returns:
An object satisfying the specified class and qualifier.
